title: West Cambridge
caption: Weld Boathouse sits along the Charles census tract with the highest life expectancy in the state, at 91.8 years. Nestled between Harvard and Mount Auburn Cemetery, this tract has a median household income over $200,000

title: A Tale of Two Allstons
caption: Stepping off Harvard property in Allston brings wealth disparities into sharp relief. In the area directly abutting HBS, the median household income is $160,000, while just a few stops down the bus line that drops to $60,000 and directly off the bus line it is $33,000.

title: The Boston Expansion that Never Was
caption: Brookline has long been one of the richest parts of Massachusetts. Adjacent towns West Roxbury and Brighton joined the growing city of Boston in the late 19th century, but Brookline refused to join in order to keep separated from the much poorer expanding city.
